{
  "text": "The anthropometric characteristics of the players in the current study are in line with other studies in elite players. Ostojic et al, 10 Sallet et al, 11 and Cormery et al 13 made a distinction between centers, forwards, and guards in the Serbian 10 and French 11,13 first division and observed body weight, height, and percentage body fat similar to those in the current study. Also in these studies the centers were taller (203-214 cm) and heavier (104-111 kg) than the forwards (194-201 cm, 89-96 kg) and the guards (184-190 cm, 82-89 kg). Similar to the current study, some studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] found that centers have a higher percentage body fat than the other positions, although this was not unequivocally found in all studies. [CITATION_4] 24 Abbreviations: PG, point guard; SG, shooting guard; SF, small forward; PF, power forward; C, center. Significant differences are indicated by different superscripts. The same superscript indicates that the parameter did not differ between the positions, P < .05. Positions with different superscripts differ significantly. 59.7 \u00b1 6.9",
